quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  27,36,"When the envoys of the queen came to Solomon, he said: \"Do you want to provide me wealth? The wealth which Allah has given me is far more than what He has given you. You may very well keep your presents"
  27,37,"Go back to your people: if your people do not submit, we will march against them with such an army of which they shall never be able to face, and we shall drive them out of their land humbled and disgraced"
  27,38,"Later on when Solomon heard that the Queen of Sheba was coming in submission, he asked: \"O my chiefs! Which of you can bring to me her throne before they come to me in submission"
  27,39,"An audacious one from the Jinns said: \"I will bring it to you before you adjourn your court; and most surely I have the necessary strength and I am trustworthy"
  27,40,"One person who had knowledge of the Book said: \"I can bring it to you in the twinkling of an eye.\" As soon as Solomon saw the throne placed before him, he exclaimed: \"This is by the grace of my Lord to test me whether I am grateful or ungrateful. Any who is grateful, surely his gratitude is a gain for his own soul, and any who is ungrateful should know that surely my Lord is Self-Sufficient, Self- Exalted"
  27,41,"Further he said: \"Without any comment to her, set her throne in her sight; let us see whether she recognize it or she is of those who cannot recognize the Truth"
  27,42,"So when the queen arrived, she was asked: \"Is your throne like this?\" She replied: \"It looks as if it is the same; we had come to know that Solomon is not only a king but also a Prophet, therefore we have already become Muslims"
  27,43,"Other deities whom she worshiped besides Allah had prevented her from believing, for she belonged to an unbelieving folk"
  27,44,"Then she was asked to enter the palace. When she saw its floor, she thought that there was pool of water, so she tucked up her skirts uncovering her legs. Solomon said. \"This is just a glossy paving of this palace.\" At this she exclaimed: \"O my Lord"